Package edu.cpp.cs.cs141.classproject

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Entity
    This interface outlines the main functions of every entity in the game.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Achievements
    This class keeps track of all existing achievements that the player could Receive and what the player has already achieved or not.
    Enemy
    This class represents an enemy in the game.
    GameEngine
    This class represents the Game Engine, where all game logic are executed.
    Highscore
    This class represents a single score in the list of existing player highscores.
    Item
    The Item class represents an item that the player can pick up.
    Main
    This class is the main class that begins the program.
    Map
    This class represents the game's map and all of the Entity objects contained within.
    Player
    This class represents the player in the game.
    Record
    This class contains all of the player's records, including top records as well as accumulative records.
    Room
    The Room object represents a room that the player can search for the briefcase.
    Shop
    This class keeps track of the upgrades that the player has bought and how much money the player has.
    UI
    The UI class represents the interface through which the player will interact with the game world.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    Entity.entityType
    This enumeration represents all of the possible types an entity can have.
    GameEngine.resource
    This enumeration represents all of the possible types of extra resource objects/files used in the game
    Item.itemType
    This field represents all possible types that the item can be.
    Map.moveResult
    This enumeration represents all of the possible outcomes of the movement of the player.
    Shop.upgrades
    This enumeration represents the four different types of possible items that can be bought in the shop.
    UI.action
    This field represents all possible actions that a player can take on a turn.
    UI.direction
    This field represents all possible directions that a player could possibly input.
    UI.mode
    This field represents all possible modes that the player can input.
